description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a Clinical Team Manager for Knowsley services within the new St. Helens &amp; Knowsley CRHT Team Assessment &amp; Home Treatment Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Crisis Resolution and Home Treatment team will offer two specialist pathways to service users experiencing severe and/or enduring mental health issues and associated risks, providing crisis management as well as support alternative to admission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have excellent communication skills where they can work effectively with multi-disciplinary teams and professionals from similar backgrounds as well as clients and their families / carers. The successful candidate will be responsible for managing a 24 hour, 7 day a week service for the residents of Knowsley whilst working closely with the clinical team manager in St Helens. Applicants should be innovative, have knowledge of performance reporting systems and have the ability to prioritise their work load effectively with strong leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will demonstrate an attitude which respects and values service users’ choice and works alongside them and their carers to ensure they are at the centre of care planning.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will benefit from:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A friendly and supportive working environment&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A leadership and governance structure specific to the clinical lead role and responsibilities to ensure supervision and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Managerial supervision and Professional Development opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bespoke Training for Crisis and Home treatment interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to &lt;strong&gt;an enhanced check with adults barred list &lt;/strong&gt;Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) Check. Successful candidates will either have a valid DBS check with the Trust or will be required to pay for the cost of the DBS Disclosure which is £47.50 for an enhanced disclosure, the cost of which will be deducted from first salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ashlie Murray&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ashlie.Murray@NWBH.NHS.UK&lt;/p&gt;
